    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1952-07-18T16:46:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1952-07-18T16:46:00-05:00" n="226"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d226">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">795.00/7—2652: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Department of the Army</gloss> to the
                        Commander in Chief Far East (<persName corresp="#p_CGMW1" type="to"
                            >Clark</persName>)</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">top secret<lb/>priority</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1952-07-18T17:46:00-04:00"
                            >July 18, 1952—5:46 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <gloss target="#t_DA1">DA</gloss> 913958. From <gloss target="#t_G31"
                        >G–3</gloss> signed <persName>Jenkins</persName>.<note n="1"
                        xml:id="d226fn1">Maj. Gen. <persName>Reuben E. Jenkins</persName>, U.S.
                        Army, Assistant Chief of Staff, <gloss target="#t_G31">G–3</gloss>.</note>
                    In further discussions here of plans to resolve <gloss target="#t_POWs1"
                        >POW</gloss> issue suggestion has been made that <gloss target="#t_UNC1"
                        >UNC</gloss> suspend release of <gloss target="#t_CIs1">CIs</gloss> and
                    increase number of persons to be repatriated by balance of <gloss
                        target="#t_CIs1">CIs</gloss> still in <gloss target="#t_UNC1">UNC</gloss>
                    custody. New total figure would then more closely aprx round number desired by
                    Communists, and might provide face-saving device for them. Upon coming into
                    effect of armistice, <gloss target="#t_CIs1">CIs</gloss> could be released to
                    return directly to their homes under principle already accepted by Communists
                    for <gloss target="#t_POWs1">POWs</gloss> whose homes are in <gloss
                        target="#t_UNC1">UNC</gloss> territory.</p>
                <p>
                    <gloss target="#t_G31">G–3</gloss> has been asked to request your comments.<note
                        n="2" xml:id="d226fn2">For <persName corresp="#p_CGMW1">Clark</persName>’s
                        comments, see <gloss target="#t_C1">C</gloss> 52204, <hi rend="italic">
                            <ref target="#d227">infra</ref>
                        </hi>.</note>
                </p>
            </div>
        </body>
